@namespace Talk.Client.Slides

@* Concept #9: how components talk. A map that frames the whole segment: params flow
   down, EventCallback flows up, and shared state (a DI service) reaches anywhere. These are the
   three mechanisms the rest of Segment C dissects in the real deck. *@
<Slide Title="How components talk to each other">
    <div class="cm">
        <div class="cm-lane down">
            <div class="cm-arrow">↓ down</div>
            <div class="cm-what"><code>[Parameter]</code></div>
            <div class="cm-desc">Parent hands values <em>down</em> to a child.<br /><span class="cm-eg">Segment B: <code>&lt;Slide Title="…"&gt;</code></span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="cm-lane up">
            <div class="cm-arrow">↑ up</div>
            <div class="cm-what"><code>EventCallback</code></div>
            <div class="cm-desc">Child raises an event back <em>up</em> to its parent.<br /><span class="cm-eg">Segment B: <code>&lt;Stepper OnStep="…"&gt;</code></span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="cm-lane any">
            <div class="cm-arrow">↔ anywhere</div>
            <div class="cm-what">Shared service</div>
            <div class="cm-desc">Any component injects it to read &amp; change the same state, no parent link needed.<br /><span class="cm-eg">this deck: <code>DeckState</code></span></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <Caption Spaced>Down and up need a parent–child wire. When two far-apart components
        need the same state, you reach for the third path.</Caption>
</Slide>

